definitions.definition: The silken structure which a spider builds using silk secreted from the spinnerets at the caudal tip of its abdomen; a spiderweb .
examples: The sunlight glistened in the dew on the web .

definitions.definition: ( by extension ) Any interconnected set of persons , places , or things , which, when diagrammed , resembles a spider 's web.
( baseball ) The part of a baseball mitt between the forefinger and thumb, the webbing .
examples: He caught the ball in the web .
The gazebo’s roof was a web made of thin strips of wood.

definitions.definition: ( usually with "spin", "weave", or similar verbs ) A tall tale with more complexity than a myth or legend .
examples: Careful—she knows how to spin a good web , but don't lean too hard on what she says.

definitions.definition: The interconnection between flanges in structural members, increasing the effective lever arm and so the load capacity of the member.
( rail transport ) The thinner vertical section of a railway rail between the top ( head ) and bottom ( foot ) of the rail.
A fold of tissue connecting the toes of certain birds, or of other animals.
The series of barbs implanted on each side of the shaft of a feather , whether stiff and united together by barbules , as in ordinary feathers, or soft and separate, as in downy feathers.
( manufacturing ) A continuous strip of material carried by rollers during processing.
( lithography ) A long sheet of paper which is fed from a roll into a printing press, as opposed to individual sheets of paper.
( glassblowing , obsolete ) A seventeenth-century unit of Rhenish glass containing 60 bunches .
( dated ) A band of webbing used to regulate the extension of the hood of a carriage .
A thin metal sheet, plate, or strip, as of lead.

subdefinitions.definition: The thin, sharp part of a colter .

definitions.definition: ( dated , US , radio , television ) A major broadcasting network .
( architecture ) A section of a groin vault , separated by ribs . (Can we clean up this sense?)
( medicine , archaic ) A cataract of the eye .

examples: Let me search the web for that.
